    "Figure 7a illustrates temperature distribution across a solar cell surface, providing insights into localized thermal effects.",
    "The color gradient depicts varying temperatures, with a minimum temperature difference of 0.68 K between the center and corresponding edge (Fig. 7a) and a maximum difference of 1.2 K between the center and corner (Fig.",
    "7b) (Zhou et al., 2015).",
    "Calorimetry, a crucial technique, provides accurate measurements of heat generated by solar cells, enabling a precise assessment of thermal effects (Table 7).",
    "Temperature-dependent characterization techniques, explored in Table 8, play a significant role in understanding and assessing thermal effects on solar cells."
